Remarks: This species has been recognised as a distinct colour form since its discovery ( Allen 1981 ;
Lundberg et al. 2000
), with strong genetic divergence noted in mtDNA studies (
Cook et al. 2012
;
Unmack et al. 2013
) and now supported with nuclear genetic markers. Somewhat subtle morphological characters support the striking colour and genetic divergence, with diagnosis apparently masked by large within site/region variability.
